`Ideal.Quotient.lift I f hfI : R ‚ßł I ‚Üí+* S`
where `f : R ‚Üí+* S` and `hfI : ‚ąÄ a ‚ąą I, f a = 0`.

This gives us the final ingredient we need to start proving the First Isomorphism Theorem.
First, we will show any homomorphism `f : R ‚Üí+* S` is well-defined as a map `R ‚ßł ker f ‚Üí+* S`.

Try filling in the missing proof using `intro`, `rw`, `apply` and/or `exact`.
-/

section universal_property
variable {S} [CommRing S]

def kerLift (f : R ‚Üí+* S) : R ‚ßł ker f ‚Üí+* S :=
  Ideal.Quotient.lift (ker f) f fun x ‚Ü¶ by
    -- We need to prove: if x is in the kernel of f, then f x = 0
    -- The assumption is x ‚ąą ker f
    -- The goal is f x = 0
    -- The definition of x ‚ąą ker f is f x = 0
    -- So we are proving f x = 0 assuming f x = 0
    -- This is trivial
    intro h
    exact h
